transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling. This is John. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, John. My name is Stanley Shaw. I put in an order and I have not got your product.

Speaker 1: Okay, what's your zip code, Stanley?

Speaker 2: 90631.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: 1031 Creek Lane.

Speaker 1: That is correct. I'm sorry for the delay, but there—you may not have seen it—but there was a message sent about this.

Speaker 2: We need to know the actual medications you take, so we need the names and then they can send it.

Speaker 1: That's all they're waiting on.

Speaker 2: What are you waiting on?

Speaker 1: The doctor and pharmacy need to know the names of the medications you take.

Speaker 2: I take very little medication.

Speaker 1: Okay, they still need to know what they are.

Speaker 2: You've already taken my money.

Speaker 1: Twice, yes. One, you opted to get more pills.

Speaker 2: That's why you were charged a second time, and then you're paying for the pills opens the doctor's visit.

Speaker 1: The doctor is okay with this pending seeing what medication you take, same with the pharmacy on sending it out.

Speaker 2: So if you're not going to share what medication you take, I can cancel it and refund you, but we have to have that medicine.

Speaker 1: All right, cancel refund.

Speaker 2: Okay, because you don't—

Speaker 1: I—

Speaker 2: Want everything we buy. One, everything we—why won't you just tell me the name of what you take?

Speaker 1: Sir—

Speaker 2: Because one, I'm doing this off my phone; my computer is down.

Speaker 1: And I don't mind doing this on my phone. If you want to do this over the phone, I'll go get my medications.

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: That's all I'm asking you to do is tell me the medicines you take, and you're telling me to cancel you.

Speaker 2: Can tell me them and I will relay the information.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I—

Speaker 1: Take a generic Lipitor, okay. I take a generic—

Speaker 2: Cozart, and my last medication I take—

Speaker 1: Is—

Speaker 2: Also item for my sleep. Those are my medications.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: So item is that we said?

Speaker 1: Yes, with a Z.

Speaker 2: Okay, I got that. Oh—

Speaker 1: Lipidm. I got it. So I'm telling both the pharmacy and doctor.

Speaker 2: I'm going to upgrade you to priority shipping because you've been waiting, so it will get to you faster now.

Speaker 1: But that's all we needed, sir.

Speaker 2: Thank you very much. Thank you. Bye. Bye.
